There is currently anxiety around the health of governor of Abia State, Okezie Ikpeazu, as he remains Coronavirus positive despite being placed under intensive care at his home in Abuja. According to findings by SaharaReporters, several tests carried out on him has continued to show that he still has the virus. The latest COVID-19 test was conducted on him last week but again returned positive, further confining the governor to Abuja where he has been for almost one month. 

Abia State Governor Okezie Ikpeazu
TOS TV The governor is said to have last had a dialysis about one week ago and is in a stable condition. Recall that on June 11, SaharaReporters revealed that Governor Ikpeazu was confirmed to have diabetes on top of a kidney failure that had further complicated his Coronavirus treatment. 



